This week on the Major Issues Podcast, the hosts revisit Batman Beyond: Return of the Joker, the dark and controversial animated film that pushed the DC Animated Universe into its most disturbing territory. Decades after Bruce Wayne hung up the cowl, Terry McGinnis faces Gotham’s greatest nightmare reborn as the Joker resurfaces with a terrifying new plan. The hosts break down the film’s chilling exploration of legacy, trauma, and identity, dive into the shocking flashbacks that redefine Batman and Joker’s rivalry, and discuss the censorship battles that shaped the movie’s multiple cuts. It’s a deep dive into one of the boldest, bleakest, and most talked-about chapters in Batman animation history.

